Vice President Mike Pence spoke about the federal response to Hurricane Harvey and the ongoing rescue and recovery efforts in Texas. He mentioned that the state is in the lead and that the role of the federal government is to provide support. Pence highlighted the deployment of over 8,000 officials from FEMA, dozens of Coast Guard helicopters and boats, and more than 3,000 National Guard troops. He also acknowledged the volunteer efforts and encouraged people to support organizations like the Red Cross. Pence assured listeners that the federal government will be there for the long haul in the rebuilding efforts and emphasized the importance of following the instructions of state and local officials. Lastly, he addressed the politicization of the situation, stating that the focus should be on rescue and recovery efforts.